<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="717">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182050" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole macracantha Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole macracantha Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macracantha">macracantha</taxonomicName>
, large thorn, alluding to propodeal spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="717">
Diagnosis Tentatively placed in the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group because of its larger size, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182050" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole macracantha Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole macracantha Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macracantha">macracantha</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181981" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cataphracta Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cataphracta Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cataphracta">cataphracta</taxonomicName>
of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33947" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole punctatissima Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole punctatissima Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissima">punctatissima</taxonomicName>
group, differing in the minor caste as follows: much larger; occiput in full face strongly convex instead of concave; pilosity denser and longer; first gastral tergite mostly shagreened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
